---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words Ending in -OUS: Adjective Strategy Guide"
  description="Master -OUS ending words in Scrabble: JEALOUS (14), NERVOUS (10), ANXIOUS (14), JOYOUS (16). Adjective suffix strategy for high scores."
  keywords="scrabble words ending in ous, ous words scrabble, jealous scrabble score, anxious scrabble, adjective words scrabble, ous suffix strategy"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Words Ending in -OUS: Adjective Strategy Guide",
    "description": "Master -OUS ending words for Scrabble with scores and adjective suffix strategy.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-30",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ous" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the highest-scoring -OUS words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "JOYOUS scores 16 points, JEALOUS and ANXIOUS each score 14, ZEALOUS scores 16, and FURIOUS scores 10. Words with J, X, or Z before -OUS tend to score highest due to premium letter values." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Why are -OUS words good for Scrabble strategy?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "-OUS words are typically 6-8 letters long, making them prime bingo candidates worth 50 bonus points. The suffix is common in English adjectives, so players can build toward them by keeping O, U, S on their rack while looking for high-value prefixes." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can you add -OUS to any adjective root in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. Only words specifically listed in the official dictionary (SOWPODS or TWL) are valid. Common roots like NERVE→NERVOUS work, but many English adjectives with -OUS are not in the Scrabble dictionary. Always verify before playing." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/letter-guides/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Letter Guides</a>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Ending in -OUS: Adjective Strategy</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">The -OUS suffix is one of Scrabble's most productive adjective endings. These words tend to be 6-8 letters — perfect bingo length — and many contain high-value letters like J, X, and Z. Learn which -OUS words score biggest and how to build toward them from your rack.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorers</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">JOYOUS (16) · ZEALOUS (16)</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">ANXIOUS (14) · JEALOUS (14) · NERVOUS (10)</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Words with J, Z, or X before the -OUS suffix consistently score highest. As 7-letter words, JEALOUS and ZEALOUS also qualify for the 50-point bingo bonus.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">High-Scoring -OUS Words</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">JOYOUS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ZEALOUS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ANXIOUS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">JEALOUS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FURIOUS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NERVOUS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FAMOUS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CURIOUS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy: Building Toward -OUS</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Keep O+U+S together:</span> When you hold these three letters, actively look for -OUS endings. The remaining 4 tiles just need to form a valid root.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Bingo potential:</span> Most -OUS words are 7 letters — ideal bingo length. JEALOUS, ZEALOUS, NERVOUS, FURIOUS all earn the 50-point bonus on top of tile scores.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Pair with power letters:</span> J, Z, X before -OUS create the highest-scoring words. If you hold J+O+U+S, you are close to JOYOUS (just need Y).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Common -OUS Words by Length</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">6 Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JOYOUS (16) · FAMOUS (11) · POROUS (8) · MUCOUS (10) · DEVOUT is not -OUS!</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">7 Letters (Bingo!)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ZEALOUS (16) · JEALOUS (14) · ANXIOUS (14) · NERVOUS (10) · FURIOUS (10) · CURIOUS (9) · SERIOUS (7)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The -OUS ending works defensively too. Playing a 6-letter -OUS word leaves no easy hook for opponents — unlike -ED or -ING words which can be extended with prefixes.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-ending-with-ous/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Ending With -OUS: Complete List</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ful/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Ending in -FUL: Suffix Strategy</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/common-bingo-endings/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Common Bingo Endings in Scrabble</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find all -OUS words from your tiles — instant, free, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
